{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"82c80bcc-db7e-436b-9193-18b42ac029ea","content":"MSTest v3 dropped support for `.testsettings` files. You need to migrate the settings to a `.runsettings` file. Your `.testsettings` has three things:\n\n1. **Assembly resolution / deployment** → `<DeploymentEnabled>` in runsettings\n2. **TestTimeout (30s)** → `<TestTimeout>` in runsettings\n3. **Code coverage collector** → `<DataCollectors>` in runsettings\n\nLet me create the replacement `.runsettings` file and update the project:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_018Mj8AaS6TfxqiGmaSGCph1","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Creating runsettings migration"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01No3hd2zHadnu3gcegQhpyG","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-04769888a34b453fa035e773bfd3aa1a/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <DeploymentEnabled>true</DeploymentEnabled>\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n  </MSTest>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n        uri=\"datacollector://microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n        assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.CoverageCollectorDataCollector, Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector, Culture=neutral\" />\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-04769888a34b453fa035e773bfd3aa1a/local.runsettings."}],"interactionId":"52547273-b34e-4cde-8db4-2a356b4d12df","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a `.testsettings` file with:\n1. Assembly resolution / test deployment settings\n2. A test timeout of 30000ms (30 seconds)\n3. A code coverage data collector\n\nIn MSTest v3, `.testsettings` files are no longer supported. The configuration needs to be migrated to a `.runsettings` file and/or MSTest v3 attributes/properties.\n\nLet me explain how to migrate each setting:\n\n1. **Test timeout**: In MSTest v3, you can set this via `[Timeout]` attribute on individual tests, or globally via `.runsettings` under `<MSTest><TestTimeout>`.\n\n\n2. **Code coverage data collector**: This goes into a `.runsettings` file under `<DataCollectionRunSettings><DataCollectors>`.\n3. **Assembly resolution / deployment**: In MSTest v3, deployment is handled differently. The `useLoadContext` setting and `AssemblyResolution` can be configured in `.runsettings` under `<MSTest><DeploymentEnabled>`.\n\nNow I'll create the `.runsettings` file with these settings.","outputTokens":717,"requestId":"0403:341029:179CDC3:1904321:6A03376A"},"id":"8461e048-6abc-4e33-8a54-69900f866285","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:21:43.600Z","parentId":"4920f88d-9a30-4005-ac1e-1ab601d3424f"}
